't even make any<br />difference to sparse whether the definition has the "pure" or not.<br />It's only when the function is used that the "pure" matters (it makes<br />the call instruction be CSE'd like any other random instruction).<br /><br />               Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
